{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"quasipoor-imposing-bluefish","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nOne-time backfill of the complexity and clone-count series by checking out sampled historical commits, running the metric tools, and writing snapshots into the going-forward store so those two trends have history.\n\n## Files\n- `scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py` — new: for sampled commits (default monthly), run `scc`/`lizard` (complexity) and `jscpd` (clones) over the tree and append snapshots via `src/rebar/metrics/snapshot.py`.\n- `tests/unit/scripts/test_backfill_complexity_clone.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nComplexity/clone are point-in-time; their movement needs seeded history, which git makes deterministic (checkout + tool run at each sampled commit). Writes through the same `snapshot.py` writer as the going-forward path so backfilled and live snapshots share one format; snapshots are labeled `source=snapshot, confidence=high` (deterministic tool output). Sampling cadence is a script arg (default monthly) — a stated default. This is an optional backfill script the core command does not depend on.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (temp git repo + stubbed tool output): the script writes one snapshot per sampled commit with the parsed complexity/clone numbers; a commit whose tool run fails is skipped and logged, not fatal.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/scripts/test_backfill_complexity_clone.py` passes: sampling 3 fixture commits writes 3 snapshots each containing `complexity` and `clone_count` keys (`jq -e`).\n- [ ] a sampled commit whose tool run fails is skipped without aborting the backfill — test asserts the run continues and logs the skip.","id":"c595-9348-d4f2-4529","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","backfill"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Backfill complexity/clone snapshots at sampled historical commits"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416836736349001,"uuid":"70e7bbb0-fc45-4aec-a80c-29f0171b156e"}